sentences: Ahn Young-mi (Korean: 안영미, Hanja: 安英美, born November 5, 1983), is a South Korean comedian.
She made her debut in KBS' Gag Concert 19th class in 2004 and is best known for her provocative wit.
In 2018, she joined the comedy-girl group Celeb Five.
Young-mi is also known as the first female MC of the South Korean talk show, Radio Star since 2019.
